stylometry:
Transportation models are used to figure out the quickest and best way to get from one point to anouther. Components of a Transportation model is each point the person or thing is traveling to, how fast it or they can go, and if there are stops along the way.

Transhipment models are used to figure out the lowest cost to ship something. The components in a transhipment problem are inventory, cost of shipping, and locations of where the item is coming from and where it is going to. A specific example of a transhipment problem is figuring out the best way to ship floral arrangements out on valentines day. Because there is such a high demand for floral arrangements on this day, the company needs to figure out the quickest way to deliver each one, and if they should bring in extra workers.

Flows are the amount of data sent over a network. Example an amount of data sent over a computer network
Nodes are the hubs in a problem an example is the computers and printers in a network.
Arcs are the connectors to the nodes. An example is that an arc is the computer wires that connect the computers and printers.
